The Herald Speeding bus overturned at corner Robert Mugabe and Chiremba Road in Harare this morning killing 2 people on the spot. Forty-eight others survived with different degrees of injuries and were immediately taken to hospital for treatment. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-462084 size-full" src="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2019/12/accident-2-1.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2019/12/accident-2-1.jpg 680w, https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2019/12/accident-2-1-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Witnesses say the Abdul & Sons Tours coach from Epworth failed to stop at a rail crossing resulting in the speeding bus failing to negotiate a sharp curve at the intersection of Robert Mugabe and Chiremba roads leading to a collision with another bus before overturning. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-462089 size-full" src="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2019/12/accident-3-2.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2019/12/accident-3-2.jpg 680w, https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2019/12/accident-3-2-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> 